Description: Sherd of rather flat shoulder of pottery transport amphora; incised inscription. Highly micaceous clay, light brown with red-brown core. Heavy wheel-ridging inside.

Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Johnston 2006b / The Delta: From Gamma to Zeta (p.29 Table 1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.089)
